          "type": "output_text",
          "text": "Here are the top recent English-language X posts discussing Gemini AI, Google Gemini, Gemini 2.0, Pro, Ultra, and related models:[[1]](https://x.com/i/status/2018403111573102976)[[2]](https://x.com/i/status/2018383919289151883)[[3]](https://x.com/i/status/2018746306101961080)\n\n### Key Highlights:\n- **Official Chrome updates on Gemini integration**: Google Chrome announced \"auto browse\" in Gemini, now available for Google AI Pro and Ultra subscribers in the US. It handles tasks like shopping or scheduling while seeking user approval.[[2]](https://x.com/i/status/2018383919289151883)[[3]](https://x.com/i/status/2018746306101961080) A demo video shows it planning a NYC trip effortlessly.[[3]](https://x.com/i/status/2018746306101961080)\n- **AI generation and tools**: Multiple creators shared videos made with Gemini-powered tools like Veo 3.1 (e.g., hyper-realistic racing scenes, zombie survival, luxury food ads) or \"Gemini Nano Banana Pro 3.0.\"[[4]](https://x.com/i/status/2017594518049305014)[[5]](https://x.com/i/status/2018163221979677025)[[6]](https://x.com/i/status/2017506033913024975)[[7]](https://x.com/i/status/2017938415627772122)\n- **Project Genie**: A new AI tool for generating explorable environments from prompts, blending Genie 3, Gemini, and Nano Banana Pro—initially for US Google AI Ultra subscribers.[[1]](https://x.com/i/status/2018403111573102976)\n- **Pricing and complaints**: Viral meme on high AI subscription costs, listing Gemini AI Ultra at $250/month alongside competitors.[[8]](https://x.com/i/status/2018061066853576816) Users lament the lack of new Ultra models post-Gemini 1 Ultra.[[9]](https://x.com/i/status/2018599132269891860)\n\nThese posts are from late Jan/early Feb 2026, showing buzz around Gemini's Pro/Ultra tiers in Chrome, content generation, and premium features.[[10]](https://x.com/i/status/2018061297871417661)",
